13 Latinorum Hernicorumque] The Latins had joined the exiled Tarquins, but, as tradition asserted, had been defeated at Lake Regillus. The original league between Rome and the Latius, which had thus been temporarily dissolved, is said to have been renewed by Spurius Cassius in 493 B.C. The same man effected an alliauce between Rome and the Hernicans in 486 B.c.: this was of great importance owing to the geographical position of the latter people, whose territory parted Rome's two great enemies, the Volscians and the Aequians.
